channel.title: Best decompiler?
channel.description: Hey guys, I got a few CLASS files in the client im re-doing that don't have their java version included. Does anyone know a good free decompiler? I checked google for a while put couldn't find one that was acceptable but free. Help an Andrew out? (:

item.title: Best decompiler?
item.dc:creator: @Andrew_Ferguson The317Guy
item.description:
@Andrew_Ferguson wrote:

blitz_9100:

I’ve used JD-Decompiler before, Its a very useful tool I used to decompile Minecraft to make mods. JD-Decompiler is free and can be found at http://java.decompiler.free.fr/ . I’ve only found it unable to decompile very big class files.

Oh that would be great, I just have to decompile a 2kb file. Thank you very much. (:
